A '''Current Sense Monitor''' is a type of monitor. It uses a high side [[voltage]] and reforms it into a proportional output [[Electric current|current]]. It has a range of 20 Volts to 2.5 Volts. It is used for portable battery products.<ref>{{cite web|title=High-side Current Monitor|url=http://www.diodes.com/datasheets/ZXCT1009.pdf|work=Diode|accessdate=November 26, 2013}}</ref>

