'''NetCentrics''' '''Corporation''', based in Herndon, Virginia, is a contractor to the federal government. NetCentrics<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://netcentrics.com/|title=Home - NetCentrics|website=NetCentrics|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> is a leading provider of enterprise IT, cloud and cybersecurity services to the federal government. The company was founded in 1995 by Bob Dixon and Bob Dougherty, the company's first CEO. In July 2017, Cynthia Barreda succeeded Dougherty as the current CEO.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/cyndi-barreda-named-netcentrics-ceo-300489517.html|title=Cyndi Barreda Named NetCentrics CEO|last=Corporation|first=NetCentrics|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref>

NetCentrics was recognized by Comparably<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.comparably.com/companies/netcentrics-corporation/awards/2017|title=NetCentrics Corporation Awards 2017|website=Comparably|language=en|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> in 2017 and again in 2018, receiving a total of 13 awards including Best Companies in DC, Best CEO, Best Company for Diversity, and Best Company Outlook. In 2018, Barreda was recognized by DCA Live as a Federal Entrepreneur<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dca-live.com/2018-federal-entrepreneurs|title=2018 Federal Entrepreneurs|website=DCA Live|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> and NetCentrics was recognized as one of the fastest growing cybersecurity companies in the DMV<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dca-live.com/2018-red-hot-cyber-companies|title=2018 Red Hot Cyber Companies|website=DCA Live|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref>. 

